C o m m e n t: The original description of 
<taxonomicName id="DCE34D77603C5A6371F96D6ACE26412A" authorityName="HERMAN" authorityYear="1981" box="[660,768,1127,1148]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Gnathymenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="1120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kestrus">
<emphasis id="2997EAE6603C5A6371F96D6ACE26412A" box="[660,768,1127,1148]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="1120">G. kestrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on 
<specimenCount id="0DE5FD7D603C5A6370F96D65C926412B" box="[916,1024,1127,1149]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1120" type="male">two males</specimenCount>
from 
<collectingRegion id="D927F816603C5A6373DF6D89CC5041CC" box="[178,374,1156,1178]" country="Ecuador" name="Pichincha" pageId="1" pageNumber="1120">Pichincha province</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="7F724B05603C5A6372EB6D89CF3941CC" author="HERMAN L" box="[390,543,1156,1178]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1120" pagination="327 - 520" refId="ref5556" refString="HERMAN L. H. (1981): Revision of the subtribe Dolicaonina of the New World, with discussions of phylogeny and the Old World genera (Staphylinidae, Paederinae). - Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 167, Article 6: 327 - 520." type="journal article" year="1981">HERMAN 1981</bibRefCitation>
). The species was subsequently recorded from three localities in 
<collectingRegion id="D927F816603C5A6372436DAFCCB741EE" box="[302,401,1186,1208]" country="Ecuador" name="Imbabura" pageId="1" pageNumber="1120">Imbabura</collectingRegion>
, Nacto, and 
<collectingRegion id="D927F816603C5A6371626DAFCF5541EE" box="[527,627,1186,1208]" country="Ecuador" name="Pichincha" pageId="1" pageNumber="1120">Pichincha</collectingRegion>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="7F724B05603C5A6371F46DAFCE4F41EE" author="ROUGEMONT G" box="[665,873,1186,1208]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1120" pagination="251 - 253" refId="ref5650" refString="ROUGEMONT G. DE (2014): A new species of Gnathymenus SOLIER (Staphylinidae: Paederinae, Dolicaonina) from Ecuador. - Entomologist's Monthly Magazine 150: 251 - 253." type="journal article" year="2014">ROUGEMONT (2014)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
